  "original_title": "Sri Lanka shares edge up in mid-day trade",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka shares edge up in mid-day trade",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s share edged up in mid-day on July 21 after opening over 1 percent stronger, brokers said as the market is waiting for key developments in the government after the appointment of the new president.",
        "The main All Share Price Index was 0.22 percent or 17.10 points stronger to 7,729.18 at 1140 hours.",
        "\u201cThe market after opening over 1 percent stronger, consolidated by the first hour of trade today as the events speculated by the investors has now been realised with the appointment of the president thereby bringing in the much needed political stability to the country,\u201d a top analyst said.",
        "\u201cNow the market has moved to wait and see again as key decisions are yet to be made.\u201d",
        "The most liquid index S&P SL20 was up 0.12 percent or 2.96 points to 2,480.77.",
        "Top gainers were Ceylon Beverage, Melstacorp and  Sunshine Holdings. (Colombo/Jul21/2022)"
      ],
